    <!-- Page Content -->
    <div id="theDiv2">
        <!-- Page Title -->
        <h1>Bachelor of Arts (B.A.) in Computer Information Systems</h1>

        <!-- Photo of Class -->
        <img src="path_to_class_photo.jpg" alt="Class Photo" class="center">

        <!-- Description of the Program -->
        <h4>Description of the Program</h4>
        <p class="text">
            The Bachelor of Arts in Computer Information Systems at St. Mary's University offers a comprehensive curriculum
            that combines technical expertise with a solid understanding of business principles. Students delve into programming,
            databases, software engineering, and more, preparing them for diverse roles in the rapidly evolving field of information systems.
        </p>

        <!-- List of Degree Plan -->
        <h4>Degree Plan</h4>
        <ul class="text">
            <li><strong>First Year:</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li>Introduction to First Year Experience (FYE) - 3 credit hours</li>
                    <li>Programming I (CS 1310) - 3 credit hours</li>
                    <li>Programming II (CS 1311) - 3 credit hours</li>
                    <li>Discrete Mathematics (MT 2306) - 3 credit hours</li>
                    <li>English Composition I (EN 1311) - 3 credit hours</li>
                    <li>Fine Arts Elective - 3 credit hours</li>
                    <li>Literature Elective - 3 credit hours</li>
                    <li>Elective - 3 credit hours</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li><strong>Second Year:</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li>Computer Organization (CS 2110) - 1 credit hour</li>
                    <li>Object-Oriented Programming I (CS 2313) - 3 credit hours</li>
                    <li>Object-Oriented Programming II (CS 2350) - 3 credit hours</li>
                    <li>Algorithms (CS 2315) - 3 credit hours</li>
                    <li>Philosophy of Man (PL 1301) - 3 credit hours</li>
                    <li>Philosophy of God (PL 2301) - 3 credit hours</li>
                    <li>Accounting Principles I (AC 2301) - 3 credit hours</li>
                    <li>Accounting Principles II (AC 2302) - 3 credit hours</li>
                    <li>Natural or Physical Sciences Elective - 3 credit hours</li>
                    <li>Calculus I (MT 2323) - 3 credit hours</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li><strong>Third Year:</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li>Operating Systems (CS 3110) - 1 credit hour</li>
                    <li>Database Systems (CS 3310) - 3 credit hours</li>
                    <li>Software Engineering (CS 3340) - 3 credit hours</li>
                    <li>Microeconomics (EC 2303) - 3 credit hours</li>
                    <li>Ethics in Computing (TH 1301) - 3 credit hours</li>
                    <li>Foreign Language Elective - 3 credit hours</li>
                    <li>Advanced Theology - 3 credit hours</li>
                    <li>History Elective - 3 credit hours</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li><strong>Fourth Year:</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li>Computer Networks (CS 3335) - 3 credit hours</li>
                    <li>Senior Project (CS 4395) - 3 credit hours</li>
                    <li>Business Elective (3000+) - 3 credit hours</li>
                    <li>Elective - 3 credit hours</li>
                    <li>Advanced Computer Science Elective (CS 43XX) - 3 credit hours</li>
                    <li>Elective - 3 credit hours</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>

        <!-- Total Number of Credit Hours -->
        <h4>Total Number of Credit Hours: 120</h4>

        <!-- Job Examples -->
        <h4>Job Examples</h4>
        <p class="text">
            Graduates of the B.A. in Computer Information Systems program at St. Mary's University are well-equipped for various roles in the
            ever-evolving IT industry. Job examples include Software Developer, Database Administrator, Systems Analyst, IT Consultant, and more.
        </p>
    </div>

